<FIRST>r a PM-Santa-Sex     12-02 0184</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Santa-Sex,0191</SECOND>
<HEAD>Accused Sex Offender Santa Claus Arrested</HEAD>
<DATELINE>El CENTRO, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Santa Claus who worked at a shopping
center booth was arrested after police found out he was a sex
offender who had violated his parole.
   Police were tipped off to the identity of the Santa Claus and
arrested him after a computer check. He had worked only one shift
at the mall, police said.
   ``The condition of his parole requires that he stay away from
unsupervised contact with children. In this case, he had actual
physical contact with children,'' Police Sgt. Tim Blankenship
Blankenship said.
   ``Salvation Army sent us a couple of applications and we picked
this individual because he had that Santa Claus look,'' said
Maurice Davis, manager of the Valley Plaza Shopping Center. ``He
came highly recommended and we had every reason to believe he was
OK.''
   Salvation Army Capt. Moses Reyes said he knew the man was on
parole but had no idea of the nature of his offense.
   ``I didn't want to pry. We look toward the future not backwards
to the past,'' he said.
</TEXT>
