<HEAD>Suspected Nazi Guard Stripped Of U.S. Citizenship</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A federal judge has issued a court order
stripping U.S. citizenship from a former Ohio man accused of
serving as a Nazi SS guard at World War II concentration camps.
   The Justice Department said Friday that the judge's order
stripping Jakob Frank Denzinger, 65, of his U.S. citizenship was
issued last Monday after the man's attorney told the government
Denzinger did not plan to respond to the charges.
   Denzinger, who had been a successful businessman in Akron, fled
the country before the Justice Department filed its complaint last
summer. He is believed to be in West Germany, the department said.
