<HEAD>AIDS Rally in Front of White House Brings 78 Arrests</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Dozens of AIDS activists who were arrested for
blocking a public roadway in front of the White House say they were
protesting what they call a lack of leadership on the issue by
President Bush.
   Many of the 78 who were arrested Friday are directors and top
officials of AIDS groups from across the country. They say more
money is needed for prevention efforts and health and social
services for victims.
   In all, about 200 protesters gathered in Lafayette Park across
from the White House at a rally marking World AIDS Day.
   Speakers at the rally mocked a statement by Bush earlier this
