<FIRST>r i AM-Lebanon-Israel     12-02 0190</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Lebanon-Israel,0195</SECOND>
<HEAD>Militiamen Shell Lebanese Town; Kill Three Shiite Moslems</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NABATIYEH, Lebanon (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Israeli-backed militia gunners shelled
the southern market town of Nabatiyeh on Saturday, killing three
Shiite Moslem people and wounding nine, police reported.
   A police spokesman said the casualties occurred during a
three-hour barrage by gunners of the Israeli-allied South Lebanon
Army militia in the crowded market town, which has a population of
about 100,000.
   The spokesman, who cannot be named in line with regulations,
said the attack started after fighters of the mainstream Shiite
Amal militia ambushed an SLA squad on a road east of Nabatiyeh.
   ``SLA casualties could not be determined, but judging by the
retaliatory artillery barrage, it seems they've had some
fatalities,'' the spokesman said.
   The 2,500-strong SLA, backed by Israeli troops, patrols a narrow
strip of south Lebanon referred to by the Jewish state as the
security zone.
   Israel carved out the 328-square-mile zone when it withdrew the
bulk of its invading army from south Lebanon in the summer of 1985,
ending a three-year occupation of the region.
   The zone serves as a buffer against cross-border guerrilla
infiltrations into northern Israel.
</TEXT>
