<HEAD>Explosives Cache Found, Suspected Basque Terrorists Questioned</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BAYONNE, France (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police were questioning three suspected
Basque terrorists Saturday after discovering a cache of explosives
in the wine cellar of a building near the Spanish border, Agence
France-Presse reported.
   About 50 police raided the apartment building in Anglet, west of
Bayonne, on Friday morning and found 18 rocket launchers and 190
kilograms of explosives commonly used by the Basque separatist
organization ETA, the French news agency said.
   ETA, which stands for Basque Homeland and Liberty in the Basque
