<HEAD>Man Killed Trying to Stop Robbery of Teen-ager</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BELL, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man who tried to stop four men from taking
a teen-ager's mo-ped was shot to death before the criminals fled
without the cycle, authorities said.
   David Guillen, 33, died late Friday at St. Francis Medical
Center.
   Sheriff's Deputy Rafael Estrada said Guillen was on his way to
use a pay phone when he saw four men in a car confront a
13-year-old boy who was pushing a disabled mo-ped.
   One man pulled a gun and demanded the mo-ped, Estrada said. When
Guillen told the group to leave the teen-ager alone, the gunman
turned and shot him, and the four fled in their car without the
cycle, Estrada added. The boy, who was not identified, was not hurt.
