<HEAD>With Summit Rdp</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   All four major networks planned live coverage of
Saturday's meeting between President Bush and Soviet leader Mikhail
Gorbachev.
   CNN planned to begin live coverage at 6 a.m. and continue with
live reports throughout the day until about 6 p.m., said CNN
spokeswoman Jane Maxwell.
   CBS, ABC and NBC all planned live coverage of the summit during
their regular evening news broadcasts.
   ABC planned to begin live coverage at about 8 a.m. and break in
